 down the values of $n$ that satisfy $7 < n \\leq 15$.\n\n(b)\n\nPip thinks $-1 < x < 8$ is the inequality represented on the number line.\n\nComplete the statement.\n\nPip's inequality is not correct because","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025March-Paper12-Q20","paper":"2025March-Paper12","qnum":20,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/25 Q20","year":2025,"session":"March","tex":"The height, h metres, of a building is 635m, correct to the nearest metre.\\\\[0.3cm]\nComplete this statement about the value of h.\\\\[3cm]\n\n  $\\leq h <$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025March-Paper12-Q21","paper":"2025March-Paper12","qnum":21,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/25 Q21","year":2025,"session":"March","tex":"(a) Find the value of $X$ when $w=5$ and $p=6$.\\\\[2cm]\n\n  \n\n(b) Make $p$ the subject of the formula.\\\\[2cm]","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"rearrange"},{"id":"0580-2025March-Paper12-Q22","paper":"2025March-Paper12","qnum":22,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/25 Q22","year":2025,"session":"March","tex":"Work out:  $1\\dfrac{5}{15}-\\dfrac{4}{5}$.\\\\[0.3cm]\nGive your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.\\\\[3cm]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025March-Paper12-Q23","paper":"2025March-Paper12","qnum":23,"marks":5,"topics":["Probability"],"s":"8.3","d":1,"cat":"probability","topic":"Combined events","qtype":"combined events","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/25 Q23","year":2025,"sessi